          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The physics simulator applies the added force until the end of the frame",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "interval. To continue exerting the force after that time, add the force",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "again with another call to the method. Handle the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/SceneEvents/Update",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "event to receive an indication of when the frame interval ends. For an",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app that renders at 60 frames per second (fps), this event occurs about",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "once per 16 milliseconds.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
